fix: status panel model display and systemd service home dir

- updateLLMStatusUI prefers the model input value over server's active_model
- model text input fires checkLLMStatus on change and updates status label on input
- modelSelect dropdown updates activeModel label immediately on selection
- install-service-linux.sh: set Environment=HOME=/var/lib/local-llm-chat in system
  service unit so the app can create its storage dir when run as the no-home service user
- install-service-linux.sh: use chown -R so leftover root-owned venv from a previous
  partial install does not block venv creation
- install-service-linux.sh: stop and disable conflicting service before installing
  (user service blocks system install and vice versa via port conflict)
- install-service-linux.sh: configure Ollama for LAN access via systemd drop-in
  setting OLLAMA_HOST=0.0.0.0; open port 11434 in firewall; show Ollama API URLs
  in install summary alongside chat interface URLs
- loadSettings() now syncs activeModel display when restoring saved model from YAML
- loadModels() now syncs activeModel display when auto-filling empty model input
- updateLLMStatusUI() now populates model input from active_model when input is empty,
  ensuring model input and status panel are always a single source of truth
